1
00:00:01,710 --> 00:00:04,087
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:23,750 --> 00:01:26,878
Quiet, Matsuda! This is not the time
to be fooling around. Knock it off.

3
00:01:27,045 --> 00:01:28,297
Yes, sir.

4
00:01:28,380 --> 00:01:31,091
This is the Kira investigation!
Stop messing around!

5
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:32,259
Sorry, Aizawa.

6
00:01:32,968 --> 00:01:34,177
-[yelps]
-[L] Matsuda!

7
00:01:34,261 --> 00:01:36,054
-I mean, please don't.
-Matsuda?

8
00:01:36,179 --> 00:01:39,099
After all, the last thing I want
is to be dead weight.

9
00:01:39,308 --> 00:01:40,350
Ryuzaki!

10
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:43,270
Is there anything I can do to help
with the investigation?

11
00:01:43,353 --> 00:01:44,354
Besides the manager thing.

12
00:01:44,646 --> 00:01:46,398
[L] Could you get me
another cup of coffee?

13
00:01:46,648 --> 00:01:47,524
[gasps]

14
00:01:48,692 --> 00:01:50,527
[snickering]

15
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:55,073
[Matsuda] I... I wanna help too!
I wanna contribute to the case!

16
00:01:56,199 --> 00:01:59,119
MATSUDA

17
00:01:59,286 --> 00:02:00,954
[romantic piano music playing]

18
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:02,372
I love you.

19
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:06,376
So please, don't tell me
you're going home now.

20
00:02:08,462 --> 00:02:11,298
Instead, say you'll stay by my side.

21
00:02:12,215 --> 00:02:15,469
Uh, Mr. Director? I can't do this.
I have a boyfriend.

22
00:02:15,552 --> 00:02:17,888
-Can we cut the love scenes, please?
-[indistinct chatter from crew]

23
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:20,015
Wait! Where'd this come from
all of a sudden?

24
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:21,933
Can't we just fake kiss or something?

25
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,602
[director] What? You're kidding.

26
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:25,312
You can't expect us to make a movie
like that.

27
00:02:25,395 --> 00:02:26,987
[Misa] If I say no, then it's no! Okay?

28
00:02:27,060 --> 00:02:28,740
-[Matsuda sighs]
-[director] Hey, come on!

29
00:02:29,441 --> 00:02:31,652
[indistinct chatter]

30
00:02:33,987 --> 00:02:36,365
[Matsuda] The Yotsuba Group's
main Tokyo office...

31
00:02:37,699 --> 00:02:39,076
And today is Friday.

32
00:02:40,702 --> 00:02:42,663
All the deaths that are beneficial
for Yotsuba

33
00:02:42,788 --> 00:02:44,790
are concentrated around the weekends.

34
00:02:45,415 --> 00:02:46,667
[Matsuda] Hmm...

35
00:02:47,042 --> 00:02:49,044
The last thing I want to be
is dead weight.

36
00:02:49,419 --> 00:02:51,421
Mogi's been incredibly efficient
from the start.

37
00:02:51,505 --> 00:02:53,882
Quiet, Matsuda! This is not the time
to be fooling around!

38
00:02:54,007 --> 00:02:54,966
Would you cut it out?

39
00:02:55,092 --> 00:02:56,134
Matsuda's special.

40
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:58,387
[L] Then, could you get me
another cup of coffee?

41
00:02:58,595 --> 00:02:59,763
Matsuda!

42
00:03:01,390 --> 00:03:02,391
[gasps]

43
00:03:03,517 --> 00:03:04,434
[Matusda grunts]

44
00:03:07,229 --> 00:03:08,105
NISHINAKA GROUP

45
00:03:08,188 --> 00:03:10,649
Matsu! Hello? Matsu, get over here.

46
00:03:10,732 --> 00:03:12,567
I guess he had to run off somewhere.

47
00:03:12,776 --> 00:03:13,735
[Misa groans]

48
00:03:21,702 --> 00:03:22,703
BADGE
RETURN SLOT

49
00:03:22,786 --> 00:03:23,745
[sighs]

50
00:03:33,547 --> 00:03:36,925
Alright, for the time being, I want you
to start going over this list, here.

51
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:38,176
Yes, sir. Right away.

52
00:03:39,970 --> 00:03:42,514
[Light] Would I punish evil doers
and criminals if I could kill

53
00:03:42,597 --> 00:03:44,516
by just seeing a name and face?

54
00:03:44,683 --> 00:03:47,185
Is that what I'd do
if I had that sort of power?

55
00:03:47,561 --> 00:03:50,313
I mean, it's true that there are lots
of people around

56
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:54,401
that the world could frankly do without,
but I don't think I'd become a murderer

57
00:03:54,484 --> 00:03:56,403
-just to change the world.
-Huh?

58
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:59,865
Surely I wouldn't do that.
No, I'm thinking too hard about this.

59
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:01,992
There's no way anyone
could murder so many people

60
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:04,661
-and not have any memory of it.
-[L] What's wrong?

61
00:04:05,078 --> 00:04:07,372
You've been staring at me
for the last two minutes.

62
00:04:07,873 --> 00:04:10,709
Wait, let me guess. You must be annoyed
because I'm the only one eating cake

63
00:04:10,792 --> 00:04:13,587
-at the moment, am I right?
-Uh, no, that's not it...

64
00:04:13,754 --> 00:04:15,672
-Here.
-Really, don't worry about it.

65
00:04:15,756 --> 00:04:17,340
-[monitor beeping]
-[Watari] Ryuzaki.

66
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:19,134
[L] Yes, what is it?

67
00:04:19,342 --> 00:04:22,429
[Watari] Detective Eraldo Coil
has just received a private request

68
00:04:22,554 --> 00:04:25,098
to investigate and reveal
the identity of L.

69
00:04:25,182 --> 00:04:29,227
Isn't Eraldo Coil supposed to be
the second greatest detective in the world

70
00:04:29,394 --> 00:04:30,645
after L himself?

71
00:04:30,854 --> 00:04:32,564
Who on earth would send such a request?

72
00:04:33,231 --> 00:04:36,276
[Watari] The man who sought out
Coil's services is Masahiko Kida,

73
00:04:36,443 --> 00:04:38,737
the head of the Rights
and Planning Department

74
00:04:38,862 --> 00:04:41,156
of the Yotsuba Group's headquarters
in Tokyo.

75
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:42,365
So it is Yotsuba!

76
00:04:43,241 --> 00:04:45,619
We know that Yotsuba
must be linked to Kira.

77
00:04:45,786 --> 00:04:47,871
If they're trying to find out
L's identity,

78
00:04:47,996 --> 00:04:50,707
it's probably because they wanna kill him
and need that information to do it.

79
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:53,794
[Yagami] This isn't good.
We're already shorthanded enough as it is,

80
00:04:53,877 --> 00:04:55,962
-and now we have to worry about Coil, too?
-[L] Mm...

81
00:04:57,589 --> 00:04:58,924
It's quite all right.

82
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:02,469
The detective known as Eraldo Coil is me.

83
00:05:02,594 --> 00:05:04,554
-[Yagami] Oh?
-[L] It's quite simple, really.

84
00:05:04,721 --> 00:05:08,558
Three of the greatest detectives
in the world, L, Coil and Deneuve...

85
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:10,310
They're all actually me.

86
00:05:11,019 --> 00:05:14,898
It's been my experience that people
who try to find me usually fall for this.

87
00:05:16,358 --> 00:05:19,444
I'll give you this strawberry
if you keep it a secret, okay?

88
00:05:20,862 --> 00:05:22,948
I'm impressed as always, Ryuzaki.

89
00:05:28,829 --> 00:05:29,746
[elevator dings]

90
00:05:37,712 --> 00:05:39,881
[Matsuda] Maybe I should leave
while I still have a chance.

91
00:05:40,215 --> 00:05:42,843
No, then there would've been
no point in coming here.

92
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:46,346
Should I wait until everyone's gone
and search their offices?

93
00:05:46,555 --> 00:05:48,765
I can't. I'd probably get caught
doing that, and then...

94
00:05:49,808 --> 00:05:52,310
Maybe I should get out of here.
[sighs]

95
00:05:52,602 --> 00:05:53,770
[Takahashi] Not this again!

96
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:55,522
I'm too tired.

97
00:05:55,981 --> 00:05:58,650
Look on the bright side,
at least it falls on the weekend.

98
00:05:58,942 --> 00:06:02,028
Might never know how long these
confidential meetings will go on for.

99
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:05,574
Can you imagine if we did this on Mondays?
That would be the worst start to the week.

100
00:06:05,657 --> 00:06:08,285
[Matsuda] Confidential meetings?
All right!

101
00:06:12,122 --> 00:06:13,456
[gasps]

102
00:06:16,751 --> 00:06:18,420
[Matsuda] The nineteenth floor!

103
00:06:20,046 --> 00:06:22,632
[grunting and panting]
I've made it this far!

104
00:06:22,841 --> 00:06:24,259
I'm gonna see it through!

105
00:06:25,677 --> 00:06:28,680
All right. I just have to get close
to him, right?

106
00:06:28,889 --> 00:06:29,806
Leave it to me.

107
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:34,352
And you want me to make sure
that we're able to breach the security?

108
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:37,689
And override the surveillance cameras
in the Yotsuba Group's head office?

109
00:06:37,772 --> 00:06:38,732
Is that all?

110
00:06:39,107 --> 00:06:43,028
Yes. At this point, it's safe to assume
that Kira and the Yotsuba Group

111
00:06:43,111 --> 00:06:44,529
are connected in some way.

112
00:06:44,821 --> 00:06:48,658
We're going to investigate Yotsuba
to determine who holds Kira's power,

113
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:51,536
and if there is more than one person
who possesses this ability.

114
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:54,497
We need a clear understanding, quickly.

115
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:21,483
We cannot let anyone from Yotsuba
figure out that we are investigating them.

116
00:07:22,067 --> 00:07:26,404
Please realize that if they do notice,
it means we won't be able to catch Kira.

117
00:07:27,781 --> 00:07:30,200
[Matsuda] Damn it.
I can't hear them clearly.

118
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:34,079
If I could only hear just one thing.
Something important...

119
00:07:35,872 --> 00:07:40,085
[muffled voices]

120
00:07:40,251 --> 00:07:41,419
[man] Let's kill him!

121
00:07:41,753 --> 00:07:43,380
[Matsuda] I just heard someone say "kill"!

122
00:07:43,546 --> 00:07:45,340
[muffled voices]

123
00:07:45,507 --> 00:07:46,716
[man] I'm sure Kira would agree...

124
00:07:46,841 --> 00:07:50,553
[Matsuda] Kira! There it is!
Kira, they said it! What's that?

125
00:07:51,012 --> 00:07:52,514
"Let's have Kira get rid of him"?

126
00:07:52,681 --> 00:07:55,183
I heard it! They really are
working with him.

127
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:57,394
I did it! This is huge!

128
00:08:00,105 --> 00:08:03,233
[grunting]

129
00:08:06,569 --> 00:08:07,904
[man] Who the hell are you?

130
00:08:09,698 --> 00:08:13,034
[L] Please be sure not to act impulsively
out of panic or haste.

131
00:08:13,410 --> 00:08:15,495
And don't take matters
into your own hands.

132
00:08:15,662 --> 00:08:17,372
-[monitor beeping]
-[Watari] Ryuzaki.

133
00:08:17,706 --> 00:08:18,957
[L] Yes, what is it?

134
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:22,961
[Watari] I have just received
an emergency signal from Matsuda's belt.

135
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:25,171
Uh, where is he?

136
00:08:25,547 --> 00:08:30,301
It seems that it's coming from within
the head office of the Yotsuba Group.

137
00:08:30,427 --> 00:08:33,805
Sorry to barge in like this!
Uh, my name is Taro Matsui.

138
00:08:33,930 --> 00:08:35,849
I'm an agent with Yoshida Productions!

139
00:08:36,224 --> 00:08:38,601
I just dropped by to ask if your company
would be interested

140
00:08:38,685 --> 00:08:43,231
in using our top multi-talented star,
Misa Amane, as your new spokesperson?

141
00:08:43,356 --> 00:08:44,232
[laughs nervously]

142
00:08:44,441 --> 00:08:45,734
[all] Hmm...

143
00:08:45,942 --> 00:08:50,321
[L] Disregard everything I just said.
We'll need to rethink our strategy.

144
00:08:51,448 --> 00:08:53,992
[sighs] Matsuda, you idiot!

145
00:09:15,263 --> 00:09:18,433
Yoshida Productions. Taro Matsui.

146
00:09:20,685 --> 00:09:22,687
He doesn't have anything
suspicious on him.

147
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:25,356
I suppose that means
he isn't a corporate spy.

148
00:09:25,732 --> 00:09:30,487
[laughs] Right, um, so please,
take Misa-Misa into consideration.

149
00:09:33,615 --> 00:09:35,575
These two are only acting as guards.

150
00:09:35,742 --> 00:09:38,244
The rest of them must be discussing
how they'll get rid of me.

151
00:09:38,745 --> 00:09:42,165
Oh, there's no way out of this.
I'm gonna be killed for sure.

152
00:09:42,624 --> 00:09:44,834
I wonder if the emergency signal
got through.

153
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:48,213
Never mind that. Even if it did,
will Ryuzaki come and save me?

154
00:09:48,421 --> 00:09:50,256
Oh, no. What's gonna happen?

155
00:09:51,216 --> 00:09:54,135
[phone ringing]

156
00:09:54,928 --> 00:09:58,556
[Shimura] Go ahead. You can answer it.
Don't say that you're here, though.

157
00:09:59,516 --> 00:10:00,934
And hold it away from your ear.

158
00:10:01,142 --> 00:10:03,520
Make sure we can listen in
on the conversation.

159
00:10:03,812 --> 00:10:04,687
Okay.

160
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:07,816
Hello?

161
00:10:08,566 --> 00:10:10,235
[L] Yo, Matsui!

162
00:10:11,528 --> 00:10:13,613
[Matsuda] Ryuzaki! [gasps]

163
00:10:14,572 --> 00:10:17,534
[L] It's me, Asahi.
It's been a while, buddy!

164
00:10:17,659 --> 00:10:19,828
[Matsuda] Asahi!
Yeah, it's been a long time.

165
00:10:19,953 --> 00:10:22,122
[chuckling] Doesn't sound
like you're out right now.

166
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:23,790
Don't tell me you're home already?

167
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:24,916
[Matsuda] Yeah...

168
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:26,668
So, you by yourself?

169
00:10:27,001 --> 00:10:29,671
Yeah. I'm by myself. What's up?

170
00:10:30,213 --> 00:10:33,216
He's not with Misa Amane right now.
Matsuda must be on his alone.

171
00:10:33,383 --> 00:10:34,384
[all] Mm-hm.

172
00:10:34,676 --> 00:10:37,178
So, do you wanna, like,
go out drinking tonight?

173
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:41,516
[Matsuda] Huh? Right now?
Oh, sorry. I'll have to pass tonight.

174
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:43,101
Oh, what's the matter?

175
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:45,854
Don't tell me your wallet
is in trouble again?

176
00:10:45,937 --> 00:10:46,938
[Matsuda] In trouble!

177
00:10:47,147 --> 00:10:50,316
Yeah, that's right.
Big troubles with money.

178
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:52,360
You know me way too well.
[laughs nervously]

179
00:10:52,694 --> 00:10:54,737
Matsuda's saying he's in big trouble.

180
00:10:54,904 --> 00:10:58,908
Oh, that's too bad. Guess I'll drag
you out some other time, all right?

181
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:00,243
See ya, buddy. [hangs up]

182
00:11:01,411 --> 00:11:02,287
Uh...

183
00:11:05,623 --> 00:11:08,793
Anyway, what do you think
about contracting Misa-Misa?

184
00:11:08,918 --> 00:11:11,421
I think she'd be a great spokesperson
for your company.

185
00:11:11,921 --> 00:11:13,089
[both] Hmm...

186
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:15,508
If you're gonna promote
one of your clients,

187
00:11:15,592 --> 00:11:17,468
shouldn't you at least
bring them with you?

188
00:11:18,887 --> 00:11:21,264
Do you expect us to believe
you're this girl's manager?

189
00:11:21,806 --> 00:11:24,893
Well, to be honest, at the moment
she's filming a movie nearby.

190
00:11:25,059 --> 00:11:27,145
Once she's finished,
I'll call her and get her over here.

191
00:11:27,312 --> 00:11:29,939
Then you can see why she'd make
a great spokesperson!

192
00:11:30,231 --> 00:11:32,775
I have to keep stalling them somehow!

193
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:37,071
Misa's cellphone is on voicemail
right now.

194
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:40,283
I left her a message and told her
to get back to me as soon as she can.

195
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:42,702
What are you planning to do, Ryuzaki?

196
00:11:43,328 --> 00:11:44,329
[L] Well…

197
00:11:45,330 --> 00:11:47,415
We have to consider that if Matsuda dies,

198
00:11:47,582 --> 00:11:49,918
our suspicions about the Yotsuba Group
would be confirmed.

199
00:11:50,376 --> 00:11:51,586
[all] Hmm...

200
00:11:52,253 --> 00:11:54,881
Let's just watch the situation
for the time being.

201
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:57,634
What should we do?

202
00:11:57,759 --> 00:12:00,345
The main question is whether
he heard anything.

203
00:12:00,511 --> 00:12:02,597
[Higuchi] If it's a possibility,
no matter how small,

204
00:12:02,722 --> 00:12:03,598
we'll have to kill him.

205
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:07,060
I'm wondering if he really did
come here just to promote his client?

206
00:12:07,310 --> 00:12:09,771
He could be an undercover cop.

207
00:12:09,854 --> 00:12:11,356
No, that can't be it.

208
00:12:11,898 --> 00:12:14,984
The Japanese police have completely
withdrawn support from the Kira case.

209
00:12:15,652 --> 00:12:17,612
Look, it doesn't really matter who he is.

210
00:12:18,071 --> 00:12:20,156
We have no choice but to kill him.

211
00:12:21,616 --> 00:12:22,867
Hmm...

212
00:12:25,078 --> 00:12:27,622
You know, now that I think about it,
it might be good to have her

213
00:12:27,705 --> 00:12:29,207
-as the face of our company.
-Huh?

214
00:12:29,582 --> 00:12:30,458
[gasps]

215
00:12:30,667 --> 00:12:34,796
Exactly. Her shoot should be done soon,
so please wait. She'll convince you.

216
00:12:38,174 --> 00:12:40,510
[yawning] I'm beat.

217
00:12:41,552 --> 00:12:42,679
[sighs]

218
00:12:43,972 --> 00:12:46,015
[gasps] I got a call from Light!

219
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:49,227
He really does worry about me
when I'm late. [chuckles]

220
00:12:50,436 --> 00:12:52,313
[phone ringing]

221
00:12:53,356 --> 00:12:54,274
Misa?

222
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:56,526
[Misa] Light! I'm sorry I've been
working so much.

223
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:57,986
I'll be finished soon, 'kay?

224
00:12:58,736 --> 00:13:01,572
Misa, you're not with Matsuda
at the moment, are you?

225
00:13:02,031 --> 00:13:05,326
Him? He's a total jerk!
He just ran off and left me here...

226
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:06,911
-[phone ringing]
-Oh!

227
00:13:07,036 --> 00:13:09,289
Hang on, I'm getting a call
on my work phone.

228
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:11,541
Oh hey, it's from Matsu.

229
00:13:11,666 --> 00:13:13,918
Misa's just received a call from Matsuda.

230
00:13:14,419 --> 00:13:17,046
Tell her to hold her phone
so that we can listen in as well.

231
00:13:18,631 --> 00:13:20,383
[Matsuda] Misa-Misa,
when you're finished filming,

232
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:22,302
come over
to the Yotsuba Group head office.

233
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:24,595
It's still tentative,
but there's a chance

234
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:26,764
you may be able to appear
in Yotsuba's commercials!

235
00:13:26,889 --> 00:13:28,224
We're working it out now.

236
00:13:28,391 --> 00:13:31,269
What? For real? You're amazing, Matsu!

237
00:13:31,436 --> 00:13:33,104
So that's what you've been up to
all this time?

238
00:13:33,396 --> 00:13:35,398
Don't worry, we're wrapping up soon.

239
00:13:35,732 --> 00:13:38,067
[Matsuda]
Great, it's just a short trip by taxi.

240
00:13:39,777 --> 00:13:40,695
Huh?

241
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:44,907
Listen to me, Light. There is a chance
that we may be able to save Matsuda.

242
00:13:45,408 --> 00:13:47,994
But we won't be able to do it
without Misa's help.

243
00:13:48,453 --> 00:13:50,830
She'll listen to you and do anything
you say, won't she?

244
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:52,498
[both gasp]

245
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:57,378
I'm Misa-Misa!
My only rule is I don't do nudes,

246
00:13:57,503 --> 00:13:59,630
but swimsuits and lingerie
are totally okay!

247
00:14:00,048 --> 00:14:01,716
It's really nice to meet you.

248
00:14:02,008 --> 00:14:04,510
[laughs nervously]

249
00:14:05,094 --> 00:14:08,264
Hmm. I gotta admit,
she is really cute in person.

250
00:14:08,598 --> 00:14:11,392
That's not exactly the main issue now,
wouldn't you agree?

251
00:14:11,684 --> 00:14:14,228
By the way, Matsu,
since Yotsuba's a big catch,

252
00:14:14,312 --> 00:14:16,814
I got the okay from our office
to have a special reception.

253
00:14:16,939 --> 00:14:19,233
-Hmm? Reception?
-[chuckles]

254
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:23,905
[all] Good evening!
We're very pleased to meet you!

255
00:14:24,322 --> 00:14:26,574
Tonight, I'll be entertaining you
as our special guests,

256
00:14:26,657 --> 00:14:28,409
along with the girls from the agency.

257
00:14:28,910 --> 00:14:31,913
Hey. Is it just me,
or is this getting weird?

258
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:33,623
Hmm, well, it can't be helped.

259
00:14:33,956 --> 00:14:36,081
-[Matsuda laughs nervously]
-Right now, we can't afford to leave

260
00:14:36,181 --> 00:14:38,002
Misa's manager alone for a second.

261
00:14:38,127 --> 00:14:40,588
Let's just go with it.
I'm gonna enjoy myself.

262
00:14:41,798 --> 00:14:44,550
-[all mumbling]
-[man] Right. Hard to go wrong with this.

263
00:14:45,051 --> 00:14:46,844
[laughs nervously]

264
00:14:47,470 --> 00:14:49,972
[Matusda] Ryuzaki and the others
will be able to watch us from here.

265
00:14:50,223 --> 00:14:51,516
This is my way out.

266
00:14:51,682 --> 00:14:54,435
-[can opening]
-[chatter and laughter]

267
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:56,813
[Misa] Here you are! Drink right up.
[chuckles]

268
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:58,439
[man] Man, we gotta do this more often.

269
00:14:58,564 --> 00:15:02,402
Hmm. Well, well.
Misa's pretty good at this sort of thing.

270
00:15:02,527 --> 00:15:04,195
[chatter continues]

271
00:15:05,405 --> 00:15:07,240
[laughs nervously]

272
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:10,701
[Matsuda] Excuse me, guys.

273
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:14,330
I gotta go to the bathroom.

274
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:25,758
Ryuzaki, are you watching this?

275
00:15:26,342 --> 00:15:28,845
-Yes.
-Look, I'm really sorry that--

276
00:15:28,928 --> 00:15:30,430
That's not important right now.

277
00:15:30,638 --> 00:15:33,975
Okay. Listen, the eight men who came here
were having a meeting to determine

278
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:35,518
who they'd get Kira to kill for them.

279
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:36,519
[all gasp]

280
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:40,022
I heard them say it clearly.
There's no doubt they're behind this.

281
00:15:40,481 --> 00:15:42,316
Yes, that is probably true.

282
00:15:42,525 --> 00:15:44,444
But if you did overhear them
and they caught you,

283
00:15:44,527 --> 00:15:46,696
then they'll almost certainly be trying
to kill you now.

284
00:15:47,155 --> 00:15:48,865
[sighs] I know.

285
00:15:49,574 --> 00:15:51,701
Do you think there's anything I can do
to save myself?

286
00:15:52,201 --> 00:15:55,538
[L] Well, luckily, you're still alive,
so we may be able to save you.

287
00:15:55,663 --> 00:15:56,706
But for that to happen...

288
00:15:57,206 --> 00:15:59,333
you will have to die
before they can kill you.

289
00:15:59,667 --> 00:16:00,543
What?

290
00:16:00,918 --> 00:16:03,421
[L] I want you to listen
to me very carefully.

291
00:16:08,885 --> 00:16:09,927
[Matsuda groans]

292
00:16:11,262 --> 00:16:12,263
No way...

293
00:16:13,055 --> 00:16:15,725
But that's... that's crazy!

294
00:16:16,893 --> 00:16:21,564
[indistinct chatter]

295
00:16:22,148 --> 00:16:24,442
And you know, our company is expanding.

296
00:16:29,614 --> 00:16:30,907
[everyone gasping]

297
00:16:31,073 --> 00:16:32,074
What the hell?

298
00:16:35,328 --> 00:16:38,623
Wow! I am so drunk!

299
00:16:39,248 --> 00:16:42,168
[Matsuda groaning]

300
00:16:42,335 --> 00:16:48,132
Oh... hi, everyone! Everyone having fun?
Good. That's great.

301
00:16:49,091 --> 00:16:52,678
Now, everyone, the moment
you've all been waiting for!

302
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:56,390
The Taro Matsui show! [laughing]

303
00:16:58,351 --> 00:16:59,852
[man] Hey, what are you doing?

304
00:17:00,978 --> 00:17:04,357
Yay! You can do it! Go, Matsu!

305
00:17:04,482 --> 00:17:06,150
All right! Here we go.

306
00:17:09,862 --> 00:17:12,281
Hey, you're drunk!
That's way too dangerous.

307
00:17:12,615 --> 00:17:17,870
Don't worry. I'm just fine.
I do this all the time. [grunting]

308
00:17:19,997 --> 00:17:21,958
[everyone gasping]

309
00:17:22,124 --> 00:17:25,628
-[Kida] The hell is he doing?
-[Takahashi] Get in here, come on!

310
00:17:25,753 --> 00:17:28,923
-[Hatori] Are you crazy, you idiot?
-[Matsuda] It's all right! No prob...

311
00:17:34,303 --> 00:17:37,765
[screaming]

312
00:17:42,228 --> 00:17:43,104
[Yagami grunts]

313
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:46,065
[thudding]

314
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:47,400
[gasping and screaming]

315
00:17:47,525 --> 00:17:48,401
He fell!

316
00:17:51,237 --> 00:17:52,488
[Mido] This can't be good.

317
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:54,490
[screams] No!

318
00:17:54,699 --> 00:17:57,618
I heard a thud, so I came out.
This is just horrible!

319
00:17:57,785 --> 00:18:00,997
-Someone call an ambulance!
-[Aiber] Geez. This sure is a crappy role.

320
00:18:01,372 --> 00:18:03,457
Look, everyone.
I think you should all just leave this

321
00:18:03,541 --> 00:18:05,251
for us to take care of and go home.

322
00:18:05,376 --> 00:18:07,878
-What? But--
-Don't worry. We'll handle it.

323
00:18:08,004 --> 00:18:10,339
Just don't forget about me
for your next campaign, okay?

324
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:13,301
Let's go. If the press sees us,
we're in trouble.

325
00:18:13,926 --> 00:18:15,011
[man] Yeah.

326
00:18:15,136 --> 00:18:16,304
[sirens wailing]

327
00:18:19,015 --> 00:18:20,725
[woman] What's going on?
Did someone jump?

328
00:18:22,852 --> 00:18:26,105
Well, we're lucky that he ended up dying
right in front of us, at any rate.

329
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:27,565
-Hey.
-[ambulance door slams]

330
00:18:34,488 --> 00:18:35,615
[chuckles]

331
00:18:36,699 --> 00:18:38,993
While I'm aware of the fact
that we're shorthanded,

332
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:42,163
I'm not very pleased about having
to do this sort of thing myself.

333
00:18:42,288 --> 00:18:44,415
Matsuda, you idiot.

334
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:47,501
[sighs]

335
00:18:59,805 --> 00:19:02,975
"Misa Amane's manager dies in fall."

336
00:19:03,601 --> 00:19:04,560
Hmm...

337
00:19:04,685 --> 00:19:05,936
[phone ringing]

338
00:19:07,730 --> 00:19:09,857
UNKNOWN NUMBER

339
00:19:10,358 --> 00:19:11,275
[Kida] Yes?

340
00:19:11,484 --> 00:19:14,820
[man] You're Masahiko Kida,
VP of the Rights and Planning Department

341
00:19:14,904 --> 00:19:16,947
at Yotsuba's Tokyo office, correct?

342
00:19:17,531 --> 00:19:19,700
[Kida] Yes, that's right,
and who am I speaking to?

343
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:25,122
I go by the name Eraldo Coil.
I'm calling to discuss my terms with you.

344
00:19:25,247 --> 00:19:26,415
[Kida gasps]

345
00:19:26,540 --> 00:19:28,876
[Ooi]
What? A two-million-dollar advance

346
00:19:29,001 --> 00:19:30,544
and eight million upon completion?

347
00:19:30,836 --> 00:19:32,171
Is he out of his mind?

348
00:19:32,296 --> 00:19:34,298
That's not all.
Even if we don't commission him,

349
00:19:34,382 --> 00:19:37,009
we have to pay him two million
just to keep him silent.

350
00:19:37,343 --> 00:19:39,136
So, he wants hush money, huh?

351
00:19:39,887 --> 00:19:41,681
If he's saying something like that,

352
00:19:41,806 --> 00:19:44,100
we should assume Coil knows
quite a bit already.

353
00:19:44,975 --> 00:19:49,563
This is getting ridiculous. I've had it!
I want out of these meetings right now!

354
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:51,607
I don't know who Kira is
and I don't care.

355
00:19:51,774 --> 00:19:54,860
I just don't wanna get wrapped up
in this and end up in jail!

356
00:19:54,944 --> 00:19:56,195
-[Higuchi] No.
-Huh?

357
00:19:56,821 --> 00:19:57,863
[Higuchi] Hatori...

358
00:19:58,239 --> 00:20:00,658
I think you're going to end up
dead tomorrow.

359
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:11,669
No, wait! I was only joking!
It's not like that!

360
00:20:13,129 --> 00:20:15,423
I'm in. I'll see this to the end.

361
00:20:15,506 --> 00:20:17,216
So what are we going to do?

362
00:20:17,341 --> 00:20:21,053
Coil is still willing to accept the job
despite what he already knows.

363
00:20:21,178 --> 00:20:24,223
Isn't is obvious? He'll become partners
with us as long as we pay him.

364
00:20:24,598 --> 00:20:26,851
His demands are exorbitant,
but we need to have someone

365
00:20:26,976 --> 00:20:28,978
as skilled as Coil on our side.

366
00:20:29,061 --> 00:20:32,064
Good point. Pay him.
It doesn't matter how much.

367
00:20:32,314 --> 00:20:34,150
Exactly, we'll just have to pay him.

368
00:20:45,703 --> 00:20:49,790
[Ooi] All right, we'll contract Coil.
Anyone have any objections?

369
00:20:49,915 --> 00:20:51,584
[all] No objections.

370
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:54,795
[Wedy] L, are you listening?

371
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:58,007
[sighs] I'm so disappointed.
I thought this would be a challenge.

372
00:20:58,174 --> 00:21:00,176
Security level here is a joke.

373
00:21:00,301 --> 00:21:02,720
They've left it all
to a single contractor.

374
00:21:03,179 --> 00:21:05,681
There weren't even any
wiretap detectors.

375
00:21:06,474 --> 00:21:09,059
It's been about a week since I first
snuck into the place.

376
00:21:09,226 --> 00:21:12,480
It looks like things have been moving
pretty smoothly since then, huh?

377
00:21:12,855 --> 00:21:14,106
We've almost got them.

378
00:21:14,690 --> 00:21:16,609
So, one of these people...

379
00:21:19,069 --> 00:21:19,945
is Kira.

380
00:21:20,196 --> 00:21:21,947
[Ooi] Well, then,
now that everyone's here,

381
00:21:22,031 --> 00:21:23,407
let's commence our regular meeting.

382
00:21:23,532 --> 00:21:26,827
[Yagami] But if they're supposed
to be eight, why are there only seven?

383
00:21:26,952 --> 00:21:32,958
TO BE CONTINUED

384
00:21:38,214 --> 00:21:43,469
[theme music plays]
